#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*A Friendly Chat*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk to your children about something that they are interested in! üòÉ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚öΩ An easy way to start talking to your children is to ask them about something they are interested in. For example, you could talk about local stories, traditions, sports, favourite books, movies, friends, music, famous people or school-related topics."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÇ You may not find everything your children share to be interesting, but it‚Äôs important to show enthusiasm and an eagerness to learn. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Paying attention to what matters to your children can make a big difference in your relationship and their happiness."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Reflect on the Positive*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Spread Positivity! üåà"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí° Together, take a minute to think about all the things you did today. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚òÄÔ∏è Take turns sharing one positive or fun thing that happened. This could be something small or big, like feeling good because you cleaned the house, took a pause to take some deep breaths, learnt a new dance move, or spent time with your family and friends."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚è∞ Try doing this every day - even more on the days it feels like you have not done anything special."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*What‚Äôs New?*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Learning is fun! üéì"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚ùì Ask your children to think of a new, fun skill you could learn together. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example, keeping a ball in the air with your foot, learning dance steps, cooking a simple meal together, practising local language phrases, sharing stories from your culture, playing local games and sports, or learning about all the countries in your region."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîÑ Take turns trying out the new skill. Make sure to praise each other and learn and play together!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üíõ Approach learning the skill in a kind and fun way, and do not judge your children or yourself for your ability in the skill."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Check-in Chat*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Actively checking in on one another helps to keep relationships healthy! ‚≠ê"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask each other questions like: ‚ÄúWhat made you happy today?‚Äù üëÇ ‚ÄúWhat was difficult today?‚Äù üëÇ ‚ÄúHow can I help you?‚Äù üëÇ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For this to help, your children need to feel safe while sharing things with you. Be open to their responses. üíö"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Older children tend to be more honest when they trust that what they say will not be used against them later."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Be kind to yourself if your children do not want to share their problems with you. üíô Often, children are afraid to share as they are scared they will get in trouble. Getting upset with them won‚Äôt help - keep showing you love them and give them time! üå∑"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Express Yourself*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Dancing makes people happy!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üåà This game can be played in pairs or as a group - stand facing each other or in a circle."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üéµ Together, choose a song, a fun sound, or a clapping pattern to follow and choose a person to start the game by creating one dance move."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÄ The person to their right must copy that dance move and add their own move to it."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚ú® Go around the circle, each person adding a new dance move."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîÑ The first one who forgets someone's dance moves or does it in the wrong order chooses the next song, sound, or pattern and starts the game again."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üéâ Have fun trying out new dance moves with this game!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*2 Truths, 1 Lie*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This is a fun, quick game, and the point of it is to learn things about each other. Make your answers as interesting as possible! üé®"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí° Everyone thinks of 3 facts about themselves. 2 must be true, and 1 must be a lie. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üî∑ Here are some examples: I hate bananas, I enjoy dancing, and my favourite subject in school was maths."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÄ Share your facts with your children and ask them to guess which one is a lie. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîÑ Now ask them to do the same, and guess theirs."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Did you learn anything new about your children, or did they learn anything new about you? üíõ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Yes, No or Maybe*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Are you tired of hearing your children say yes, no, or maybe to all of your questions? Turn your chat into a game, and don‚Äôt allow one-word answers. üéà"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üî¥ Older children are known to give one-word answers to avoid talking. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí° When you would like to really know how your children are doing, you can turn your chat into a game. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚≠ê Take turns asking each other questions. The only rule is that you cannot use one-word responses like Yes, No, Maybe, Fine, and Okay."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚öΩ You can ask about things your children like or what they did today. For example, how was your day? What are you excited about? Is there anything worrying you?"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîÑ It is important to let your children ask a question as well. Trust is built when your children can see that you are also sharing your life with them and not only trying to learn about their life."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Get Active*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Exercise is a great way to spend time together, and it is so good for your health. üå± Find a sport or exercise activity that both you and your children want to do and try it out together! Be mindful of the safety of the space you are using for exercise. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚è∞ Even walking for 10 minutes a day is good for you. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚öΩTogether, try walking, running, dancing, stretching, playing games like hide-and-seek, or any other physical activities you enjoy."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üèÜ Together, think of ways to make it even more fun. Can you run to a certain point? Take turns being the coach? Can there be a small, free reward like getting to decide the next activity?"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üåà Exercise becomes easier and more enjoyable the more you do it. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîÑ If you or your children do not like the first type of exercise you pick, try a new way to exercise."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Take a Pause With Your Children*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take a pause with your children. This helps them deal with stress in a healthy way!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚è∞ You could take a pause together at any time, or you could try at a specific time like before meals or bedtime."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÇ Sit down together and close your eyes. Listen to your breath as it goes in and out. Notice how you feel. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚≠ê Take 5 more deep breaths."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÄ When you are ready, open your eyes again. Do you feel any different? "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚è∏ Ask your children what it was like to take a pause. Listen and accept whatever they say about it."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*This Is Who I Am*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Self-esteem is the way you value yourself, either in a positive or negative way. Helping your children have high self-esteem is a recipe for success! üèÜ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚≠êShare with your children 3 things you like about yourself!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ Ask your children to tell you 3 things they like about themselves."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example, I am great at treating others kindly. I am great at styling my hair. I am great at football. ‚öΩ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If any of your children do not feel comfortable sharing these, ask them to write them down. üìù"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Weekly Goal Setting*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let‚Äôs set some goals ‚≠ê"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚è∞ It can be helpful to set smaller weekly goals that are easier to reach, especially when life feels uncertain. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid " "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí°Ask each of your children for one goal that they would like to achieve this week. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîÑ Make sure this goal is *specific* and *achievable* to reach in 1 week, like: practising deep breathing for 5 minutes every day, exercising for 10 minutes three times a week, journaling feelings every night, or spending quality time with family or friends daily."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üíö You can also share your own weekly goals with your children and support each other so you can both achieve your goals."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üéâ Make sure to praise and celebrate your children for their hard work towards reaching their goals."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üîî If your children do not reach their goals, that is okay. Discuss with them the steps they still need to take or how they could reach it a different way."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*One-on-One Time*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üíö Spending time just with your children and taking an interest in them can improve your relationship. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÄ When your children are playing alone or occupying themselves, join them and show interest in what they are doing."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÇAsk questions about their activity and listen to them."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let your children lead the activity and follow them to build their confidence and autonomy. üòÉ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëÄ Say what you see - describing everything and supporting your children‚Äôs actions."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Be positive, praise your children and enjoy spending this time with them. üòÉüíö"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Animals*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üß∏ **Active Animals** "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take turns with your children doing animal actions. You might hop like a frog, stretch like a cat, run like a dog, slither like a snake, or flap like a bird. Add your own actions and animals!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí°**All the Animals We Can Think Of** "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Think about groups of animals and talk about them with your children! "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "What are all the animals we can think of that have feathers? What are all the animals we can think of that eat plants? üå± What animals can we think of that lay eggs?"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Active Counting*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üëã Clap, hop, jump: Play the following game with your children. Make it active!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ Clap hands 1 time. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ Clap hands 2 times."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ Jump 1 time. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ Jump 2 times."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ Hop 1 time."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ Hop 3 times."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí° Can you hop, then jump, then clap? "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üèÜ Can you clap twice, jump once, and hop three times?"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üí° Remembering Instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take turns playing a game where you give 2-3 instructions that the other person has to remember to follow. Make sure physical movement is included!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Hop twice, turn around."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Jump to the kitchen, pick up a spoon, then run back. ‚úÖ"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "*Active Songs*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üòÉ Young children love physical games but they need reminders about how to play. üí°"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "üéµ Songs with movements are fun and active and give instructions on how to move!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Sing songs to your children in which they have to follow instructions like:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚úÖ Start and stop ‚ùå"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚¨áÔ∏è Slow down and speed up ‚¨ÜÔ∏è"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Today's tip is about caring for yourself. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In tough times like these, it's normal to feel overwhelmed. Remember, it is important to take a moment for yourself, no matter how small."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Taking care of yourself helps you be there for your children during tough times."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 4 tips on how to take care of yourself:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ **REST**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Look after yourself as much as possible and try to rest when you can."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Try to do something that helps you relax."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **CONNECT**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Connect with loved ones as often as you can."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Find someone you can talk to about how you are feeling."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **BREATHE**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Take a moment each day to listen to your breath as it goes in and out."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Losing your temper? Breathe in and out slowly five times."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "4Ô∏è‚É£ **CARE**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Make sure to take care of yourself so you can feel better and be there for your family. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Remember to praise yourself each time you take steps to cope."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚úÖ 100%"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Remember, you're doing the best you can. Be proud."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This tip is about making a routine for your children. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When we are in crisis, things can feel unfamiliar. Having routines helps your children feel safe and stable."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When you do the same things every day, it makes life more familiar for your children. It also makes them feel less worried and more secure."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips on making routines to spend time together with your children:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ **DO IT DAILY**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Even when it feels hard, try to have some activities that you and your children do every day for yourself and your children."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If you can, help children with daily routines like eating together and cleaning."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **PLAY EVERY DAY**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Try to set aside time to play or spend quality time with your children every day. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Playing with and talking to children for a few minutes every day helps them feel secure."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask children what they would like to do."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Listen to them, look at them, and give them your full attention."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **PRACTISE BEING CALM**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Our children learn calmness and kindness from us."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Every day, try telling yourself a calming message. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Try ‚ÄúI can do this, I am trying my best.‚Äù"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Small amounts of time can help children feel safe and loved."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "After this lesson, you can type {PLAY} to get some activity ideas to do with children."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚úÖ‚¨úÔ∏è"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You‚Äôve completed 50% of this tip! Press NEXT to continue."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are some regular activities you might want to try to do with your children:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Eat one meal together"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Getting ready to sleep"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Exercise daily"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Daily play activities"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "‚úÖ‚úÖ 100%"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Parenting is not always easy. Well done for doing the best you can."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This tip is about helping your children cope with crisis. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "It is normal to be worried about your children, especially during tough times   "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Children might face emotions and challenges they don‚Äôt know how to handle."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "There are things you can do to help them feel better now and make them stronger for the future."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips on how you can support your children during tough times:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ **LISTEN**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Children may be scared, confused and angry. They need your support."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Listen to your children when they share how they are feeling."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tell them whatever they are feeling is okay, and give them comfort."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **PRAISE YOUR CHILDREN**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask children to help with day-to-day tasks, such as making food or cleaning."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Praise them for trying or doing well. This encourages helpful behaviour."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Praising children shows them that you notice and care."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **PRAISE YOURSELF**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Every day before you sleep, praise yourself for trying to help your children cope."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thinking of even 1 thing you are proud of can make a difference!"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Remember to also praise yourself for doing the best you can do."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This tip is about helping your children when someone dies. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Losing a loved one is painful for everyone, including children. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Children may feel overwhelmed and upset when someone dies."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talking to your children about death can be hard, but it will help them make sense of what is happening."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips on how to help your children when someone dies:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ **BE CLEAR**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In simple words, tell them the person has died and will not come back."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If one of their caregivers has died, tell children who they will live with and who will look after them ‚Äì they often worry about this."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **ACCEPT FEELINGS** "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "There is no right way for a child to react to loss. Children may act happy but still feel sad."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Listen to your child and tell them whatever you are feeling is okay."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **SAY GOODBYE**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Do something together to say goodbye to the person ‚Äì a song, letter or prayer."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let us understand how children of different ages react to death."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Small children under the age of 5 years may ask if the person who has died is coming back."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "They might hold onto you or other caregivers more or start doing things they used to do when they were younger, like wetting the bed."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Older children between 6 and 11 years old may ask more questions and want to understand what happened."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "They may show their grief through anger and experience physical aches or pains."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Adolescents and young teenagers from around the age of 12 years will wonder about why things happen."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Their reactions will vary and can include lack of interest, anger, extreme sadness and poor concentration."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Parenting is full of difficult conversations. Take a moment to care for yourself."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "This tip is about protecting our children from sexual violence. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "During difficult times, children are more likely to face dangers like sexual violence."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Sexual violence means someone is forced into sexual activities they don't want to do."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "By listening in a supportive way and talking openly with your children, you are helping them to stay as safe and well as possible."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips for protecting your child from sexual violence:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ *NO IS OK!*"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Teach your child that no one has the right to touch them or make them uncomfortable."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Practice saying \"no\" loudly and strongly together. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Remember, you can do this with words and with body. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talking about this with your child helps protect them."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **TELL AN ADULT**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tell them that abusers often trick children by asking them to keep sexual violence a ‚Äúsecret‚Äù."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Remind them that they don‚Äôt have to keep secrets from their parents."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **COMFORT YOUR CHILD**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If your child tells you about sexual violence, trust them."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Reassure them it‚Äôs not their fault and they are safe and loved."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You can type {HELP} for resources if your child shares sexual violence with you."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Talking about sexual violence with your children will go a long way to protect them. It is not easy but necessary. They are lucky to have you. Be proud of yourself."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Keeping children safe can feel overwhelming, especially when dealing with unexpected challenges."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "In such moments, having a clear plan will help you and your children know what to do to be safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Press Play ‚ñ∂Ô∏è to learn 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips on how to keep your children safe in an unsafe situation."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Press Play ‚ñ∂Ô∏è to learn 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips on how to keep your children safe in an unsafe situation:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ **TALK**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **PLAN**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **ASSURE**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 3Ô∏è‚É£ tips on how to keep your children safe in an unsafe situation:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk to children about what is happening in a way that they can understand."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Talk to them about things that are not safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Identify a meeting point and make a plan in case you get separated."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Keep children with you or with someone you trust all the time."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Planning with children helps them feel safer too."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Assure your children that you will do everything to keep them safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Encourage them to share anything that worries them with you."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Be proud of your efforts and try to take care of yourself too."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Remember that you are not alone and that there are things you can do to keep your children safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Planning to leave your home during a crisis can be hard because you might not have much time to be ready. "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "There are ways to make sure you have what you need to keep your children safe while travelling."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "When your children see that you're prepared, it can make them feel more stable even when things around them seem uncertain."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Press Play ‚ñ∂Ô∏è to learn 5Ô∏è‚É£ tips to help you get ready to travel with children in a crisis situation."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Press Play ‚ñ∂Ô∏è to learn 5Ô∏è‚É£ tips to help you get ready to travel with children in a crisis situation: "
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "1Ô∏è‚É£ **IDENTIFY PEOPLE YOU TRUST**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "2Ô∏è‚É£ **PROTECT YOUR DOCUMENTS**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "3Ô∏è‚É£ **PLAN**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "4Ô∏è‚É£ **COMMUNICATE WITH YOUR CHILD**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "5Ô∏è‚É£ **MAKE AN IDENTITY TAG**"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Here are 5Ô∏è‚É£ tips to help you get ready to travel with children in a crisis situation:"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Write the full name & phone number of you and three people you trust."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If you need help with writing, ask someone for help."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Make backup copies or photos of all your identity documents and keep them safe"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tell someone you trust your travel plans, where you are and who you are with."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "If a child has a mobile phone, save your number and those of a few trusted people."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Explain to your child how they should behave when at checkpoints (i.e., be quiet, do not leave the vehicle)."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Hide money or bank cards in different places, in case you lose your bags. Being prepared takes hard work."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Make up a song with your child that has your full name, phone number, and number of someone you trust. Go over it every day so they remember it."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Tell your child where you're going and why in a way they can understand and handle."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Let your children take a comfort item from home with them before leaving if possible."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "You will need something to write on, like paper or cardboard."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Ask someone you trust to help you if you need help."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "On one side, write your child‚Äôs full name and phone number of caregivers."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "On the other side, write any medication your child needs, any special needs or disability."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Cover the tag in plastic or a waterproof bag"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Hide the tag in something your child always wears (e.g., their pocket, or shoe)"
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Thank you for joining us. Everything you do is protecting your children. Well done."
msgstr ""

#. type=text
msgctxt "text"
msgid "Having to travel with children during a crisis can feel scary and hard. "
